article.headline: Nebraska 62, TCU 50
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Paul Velander came off the bench to score 11 points to help lead Nebraska to a 62-50 victory over TCU Wednesday night. Nine of Velander's points came off 3-pointers. Toney McCray and Steve Harley each added nine points for the Cornhuskers (2-0). Nebraska used a 14-3 run in the final five minutes of the first half to take a 37-24 lead at halftime. TCU hit only 4 of its 21 field goal attempts in the first half. TCU (1-3) could get no closer than seven points in the second half. Kevin Langford scored 19 points for TCU, 13 of those at the free-throw line.
